String: Client: Baudin (House, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Baudin asks for a piece of coeurl meat. He offers a crest of Davoi in return.
Client: Baudin (House, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Help rid Baudin's sister of the demon that has possessed her.
Client: Galmut (House, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Galmut is running out of oil for the clock tower. The Tenshodo might have some in stock.
Client: Derrick (Chamber of Commerce and Industry, Lower Jeuno)Summary: The famous clock tower of Jeuno is scheduled for demolition. Gather enough signatures to save it.
Client: Brutus (Chocobo Stables, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Help nurse the chocobo back to health. It seems to have suffered both mentally and physically. Gausebit wildgrass may do the trick.
Client: Dietmund (Merchant's House, Lower Jeuno)Summary: To cure Dietmund's son of his affliction, go to Qufim Island. Once there, find the flower that only blooms at night, and bring back its roots.
Client: Ilumida (House, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Ilumida wants to light a candle in memory of her husband. Bring her one from the Temple of the Goddess.
Client: Panta-Putta (Merchant's House, Lower Jeuno)Summary: You are to bring Panta the popular Wonder Magic Set. Don't say a word to his family, or else.
Client: Panta-Putta (Infirmary Monberaux, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Panta wants you to take the Two of Swords to the Manustery in Windurst to restore the Cardian's magical power.
Client: Kurou-Morou (Fortunetellers, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Create your own crystal ball to have your fortune told.

Client: Chululu (Fortunetellers, Lower Jeuno)Summary: You must gather one of each kind of Tarut card--the Hermit, the King, Death, and the Fool--before your fortune can be told. Trade with your fellow adventurers to collect the full set.

Client: Chululu (Fortunetellers, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Collect the complete set of Tarut cards by trading with your fellow adventurers, that you might help spread the joy and wisdom of fortune-telling across the realm.
Client: Lewenhart (Song Runes, Buburimu Peninsula)Summary: Copy the lyrics from the ancient monument to a sheet of parchment.
Client: Mertaire (Merry Minstrel Meadhouse, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Show the desperate bard Mertaire the words to the song.
Client: Chululu (Fortunetellers, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Chululu needs you to dispose of what she forgot to put out on rubbish day.
Client: Kurou-Morou (Fortunetellers, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Kurou-Morou has thrown his precious hairpin into the rubbish, so he needs a new one made.
Client: Zauko (Lower Jeuno)Summary: Zauko needs someone to help light the streetlamps.
Client: Naruru (Merchant's House, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Naruru can't find her favorite cooking pot. Get her a new one from the Windurst Culinarians' Guild.
Client: Ghebi Damomohe (Neptune's Spire, Lower Jeuno)Summary: To join the Tenshodo, you need either a membership form or an invitation from a current member.
Client: Panta-Putta (Merchant's House, Lower Jeuno)Summary: The Two of Swords has gone missing. Nobody knows where he has gone off to.
Client: Brutus (Chocobo Stables, Upper Jeuno)Summary: You have taken your first step. The path of the beastmaster lies before you.
Client: Lewenhart (Song Runes, Valkurm Dunes)Summary: You have taken your first step. The path of the bard lies before you.
Client: Galmut (House, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Help the dejected Galmut by saving his clock tower.
Client: Rouliette (Temple of the Goddess, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Bring a lanolin cube to Rouliette so she can make you a candle.
Client: Karl (Port Jeuno)Summary: Karl will trade you a Wonder Magic Set for a white rock.
Client: Radeivepart (Peace Monument, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Prove you are worthy to receive the map of Castle Zvahl by bringing a flame degen back to Radeivepart.
Client: Imasuke (Gate to Qufim, Port Jeuno)Summary: Present Imasuke with a kaiser sword to receive a map of Delkfutt's Tower.
Client: Garnev (Tenshodo, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Garnev will trade you some clock tower oil for a gold Orcmask.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix promises to enlarge your pack if you bring him the following: some dhalmel leather, a steel ingot, a square of linen cloth, and a peridot.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix promises to enlarge your pack further if you bring him the following items: some ram leather, a mythril ingot, a square of wool cloth, and a turquoise.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix promises to enlarge your pack even more if you bring him the following: some tiger leather, a gold ingot, a square of velvet cloth, and a painite.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix will make your pack as big as a gobbiebag if you bring him the following: a cermet chunk, a darksteel ingot, a square of silk cloth, and a goshenite.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix will make your pack bigger than a gobbiebag if you bring him the following: a square of bugard leather, a paktong ingot, a square of Moblinweave, and a rhodonite.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix will make your pack even bigger if you bring him the following: a square of balloon cloth, a shakudo ingot, a high quality eft skin, and an iolite.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix will make your pack even bigger if you bring him the following: a square of lynx leather, an adaman ingot, a square of rainbow cloth, and a deathstone.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix will make your pack even bigger if you bring him the following: a square of smilodon leather, an electrum ingot, a  square of cilice, and an angelstone.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix will make your pack even bigger if you bring him the following: an orichalcum ingot, a square of peiste leather, a square of oil-soaked cloth, and an oxblood orb.

Client: Bluffnix (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bluffnix will make your pack even bigger if you bring him the following: a molybdenum ingot, a square of griffon leather, a square of foulard, and an angel skin orb.
Client: Sattal-Mansal (Tenshodo, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bring back a Quadav charm and Sattal-Mansal will trade a coruscant rosary for it. Only then can you enter the depths of Beadeaux.
Client: Sattal-Mansal (Tenshodo, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Bring back a Quadav augury shell and Sattal-Mansal will trade a black matinee necklace for it. Only then can you enter the depths of Beadeaux.
Client: Llamrei (Dining Hall, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Llamrei will award you with a key the archduke discovered if you bring the required items.
Client: Llamrei (Dining Hall, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Llamrei will award you with a key the archduke discovered if you bring the required items.

Client: Vola (Tenshodo, Lower Jeuno)Summary: To receive your brown belt, find a nue fang, a morbolger vine, and a dodo skin. Only then will you be worthy.
Client: Guttrix (Goblins' Goblet, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Each week, a different magical pattern appears inside a treasure chest somewhere. Give it to Guttrix and he'll reward you.
Client: Zona Shodhun (Residential Gate, Port Jeuno) Summary: Zona likes pretty flowers and pebbles. Find some for her. Perhaps something yellow?
Client: Guslam (Durable Shields, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Gauntlets wrought by Borghertz, the legendary craftsman, lie hidden somewhere in Vana'diel.
Client: Guslam (Durable Shields, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Gauntlets wrought by Borghertz, the legendary craftsman, lie hidden somewhere in Vana'diel.

Client: Brutus (Chocobo Stables, Upper Jeuno)Summary: The Tenshodo wants Brutus's opinion on which axe they should carry in their stores. Brutus has asked you to test one of the axes until its blade has gone dull.
Client: Brutus (Chocobo Stables, Upper Jeuno)Summary: The guiding bell is hidden somewhere inside Delkfutt's Tower. Brutus wants you to bring it back for his deceased chocobo.
Client: Brutus (Chocobo Stables, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Many animals conscripted during the war did not return. Brutus wants you to put their souls to rest.
Client: Dietmund (Merchant's House, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Something is amiss in the Eldieme Necropolis. Observe the fiends and find a solution.
Client: Mertaire (Merry Minstrel Meadhouse, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Take Mertaire's bracelet to Ranguemont Pass and immerse it in the Waters of Oblivion.
Client: Bki Tbujhja (Merry Minstrel Meadhouse, Lower Jeuno)Summary: A certain post is rotated at the meadhouse. Now, it's your turn.
Client: Imasuke (Qufim Tunnel, Port Jeuno)Summary: Solve the riddle of the ring, and find the truth behind it.
Client: Ilumida (House, Upper Jeuno)Summary: A "moondrop" from the Boyahda Tree is required to open the chest Ilumida's late husband left for her.
Client: Atori-Tutori (Tenshodo, Lower Jeuno)Summary: If you want information on the black belt, you need to first bring back what Atori-Tutori wants.

Client: Migliorozz (Temple of the Goddess, Upper Jeuno)Summary: The Tenshodo has opened the ruins of Pso'Xja to adventurers. Migliorozz has asked you to perform a task involving the gate that lies in the deepest part of the southwest tower of the ruins.
Client: Taillegeas (Dining Hall, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Taillegeas has asked you to collect several items desired by guests of the duchy.

Client: Omer (Market Bridge, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Help Omer retrieve his prized fishing rod that was stolen from him by an Elvaan girl. Apparently the rod was lost when she fished up a monster out on Qufim Island...

Client: Odasel (Gems by Kshama, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Odasel wants to find out which of the three beauties in the gem store has feelings for him. According to a passing Elvaan girl, a jewel known as the "Chameleon Diamond" could help solve his dilemma...

Client: Nevela (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Nevela wants to hear the story surrounding the birth of a chocobo in the Upper Jeuno stables. The chocobo's mother is said to have been from the stables in Bastok...
Client: Harith (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: The mysterious "society" that Harith works for is supposedly performing research on a strange life form known as the Empty.
Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Luto wants you to find out if the person you chose from her list is holding a certain mirror.
Client: Laurana (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Laurana's daughter has gone missing. She is a young girl with blonde hair, and was wearing a brown dress and a brown cap.

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Luto has recently discovered that another mirror bearing strange properties exists in the world. It is supposedly somewhere in San d'Oria and she wants you to go look for it.
Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Luto wants you to search the Optistery library in Windurst for a book that can help her repair the broken mirror.

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Luto has asked you to locate a special metal that can be used to repair the broken mirror. According to her research, this substance can only be found inside an extremely rare species of slime.
Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Palometa still lies in cursed slumber. You must find a way to save her!
Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Save Palometa from her mysterious captor.

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: A friend of Luto has used a magical costume kit to change into a child, but now he can't return to his original form. Luto wants you to help find a way to change him back.

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Your adventuring fellow is in the hospital after being attacked by a monster in Qufim. You should go make sure your friend is not too badly hurt.

Client: Esha'ntarl (Audience Chamber, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Bahamut returned to the heavens following the defeat of the Keeper of the Apocalypse, but recently he was witnessed descending upon Cape Riverne with an army of wyrms. Go to Bahamut and find out his intentions.
Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Your adventuring fellow is acting strangely. Talk to Luto to see what you can find out.

Client: Esha'ntarl (Audience Chamber, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Strange readings have been recorded from the Emptiness surrounding the mothercrystals. Travel to the crags of Holla, Dem, and Mea and investigate the coordinates where this phenomenon is occurring.

Client: Esha'ntarl (Audience Chamber, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: The next incarnation of the Keeper of the Apocalypse is attempting to cross over into Vana'diel. Sing the  Lay of the Immortals before the fifth mothercrystal and put an end to this threat once and for all!
Client: Ajithaam (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: The mercenary company "Salaheem's Sentinels" has asked you to help recruit new members.
Client: Faursel (Tenshodo, Lower Jeuno)Summary: If you want to ride the mercenary transport ship from Mhaura, you must bring the required items to the Tenshodo.
Client: Brutus (Chocobo Stables, Upper Jeuno)Summary: A chocobo has run away from the stables in Upper Jeuno, and Brutus wants you to help bring it back.
Client: Laila (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Laila has asked that you bring her a stardust pebble before she'll consider allowing you to join Troupe Brilioth.

Client: Laila (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Troupe Brilioth is aiming for a dance style that will captivate and enchant. Work out how to take your dancing to the next level, then come back and show Laila.

Client: Laila (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: As a child, Laila had an inspirational encounter with a piper at Lake Mechieume in Jugner Forest. In order to become a great dancer like Laila, you should seek a skilled musician to play a tune for you.
Client: Laila (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Deliver Wyatt's proposal to the owner of the music shop in Bastok Markets so he can pass it on to Valeriano.
Client: Laila (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Obtain a "dancer's testimony" and bring it to Laila.

Client: Rakuru-Rakoru (Holy Owen's Square, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Rakuru-Rakoru from the Orastery wants you to collect research data by defeating all the monsters recorded in the Data Analyzer and Logger EX (Dale).

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: As a test of strength, you have agreed to meet your fellow in single combat at the Qu'Bia Arena. Who will emerge victorious in this face-off between friends?

Client: Zalsuhm (Muckvix's Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Self-styled leading researcher of mystical artifacts, Zalsuhm, claims that the weapon you acquired deep within Nyzul Isle conceals immense power. Wielding the now unlocked weapon will cause a magical evolution to take place...eventually.

Client: Maat (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Apparently, your innate limits can be breached by acquiring the necessary items.
Client: Maat (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Collect three stones of frigicite from fiend-infested caverns in the north. Bring them to Maat to further expand your innate limits.
Client: Maat (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Your innate limits can be pushed further by collecting the crests of the Orcs, the Quadav, and the Yagudo.
Client: Maat (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Use Maat's hints to search out four people who will trade you a strange stone for a Kindred's seal. Only then will you know your true limits.
Client: Maat (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Maat has issued a final challenge to test your limits. Return with the item he has requested and the trial will begin.
Client: Maat (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: After clearing all of Maat's final challenges, you will finally learn his secret...

Client: Nomad Moogle (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Has the enigmatic nomad moogle truly ascertained ancient secrets that will allow you to exceed long-standing limits? Acquire five Kindred's seals and three merit points and see for yourself!

Client: Nomad Moogle (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: The nomad moogle claims to have perfected another procedure that will send your powers burgeoning to even greater heights. Acquire five Kindred's crests and four merit points if you fancy yourself ready for the undertaking.

Client: Nomad Moogle (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: The nomad moogle claims to have perfected another procedure that will send your powers burgeoning to even greater heights. Acquire ten Kindred's crests and five merit points if you fancy yourself ready for the undertaking.

Client: Nomad Moogle (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: The nomad moogle has invited a Tarutaru of questionable affiliation to supervise his latest physical enhancement project. Acquire the items requested as well as ten merit points if you have the stomach to proceed.
Client: Nomad Moogle (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Atori-Tutori has a present for you, but first you must procure the seasoning stone he seeks...

Client: Nomad Moogle (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Atori-Tutori has deigned to present you with your final challenge--a sparring match with the smug Taru himself. Acquire a soul gem and soul gem clasp and meet your opponent for the ultimate showdown.

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: You have been entrusted with lifting the spirits of your comrade, who has been mired in a crisis of confidence since suffering defeat at the Qu'Bia Arena. Head to the Ru'Lude Gardens, where the Magian Mooglehood will offer their assistance.
Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Another invitation has arrived from the Magian Mooglehood. Strike forth with your comrade in pursuit of yet loftier heights of power!

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Your comrade's zeal for self- improvement knows no limits, and the Magian Mooglehood stands ever ready to assist in this endeavor. Make your way to Ru'Lude Gardens, where a new challenge awaits!

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: The Magian Mooglehood has requested the help of you and your companion once again, just in time to quench that thirst for knowledge and power! Venture to the Ru'Lude Gardens to receive a taste of what's to come!

Client: Luto Mewrilah (Artisan Bridge, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Appease the Magian Mooglehood by slaying some brutes and appease your new client by collecting twenty Kindred's crests on the way to bettering yourself and your partner!
Client: Atori-Tutori (Grand Duke Palace, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Amass fifteen merit points to fulfill your contract with Atori-Tutori and open the path to heretofore unseen powers...

Client: Mawl'gofaur (Audience Chamber, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: A yet-unstable planar rift has been sighted in the Valkurm Dunes. Engage and eliminate any Voidwalkers that may emerge from this dimensional disturbance.

Client: Mawl'gofaur (Audience Chamber, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: A yet-unstable planar rift has been sighted on Buburimu Peninsula. Engage and eliminate any Voidwalkers that may emerge from this dimensional disturbance.

Client: Anastase (Main Promenade, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: A research expedition from the Sacred City of Adoulin is seeking collaborators. They require information about geomagnetic founts in various areas to assist in the testing of their mystical devices.
Client: Anastase (Main Promenade, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Help find geomagnetic founts in the areas divined by eccentric clairvoyant, Quwi Orihbhe.
Client: Anastase (Main Promenade, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: More geomagnetic founts have been discovered throughout the Middle Lands. Record any relevant data and report back to Anastase.

Client: Anastase (Main Promenade, Ru'Lude Gardens)Summary: Some fount data has destabilized, causing travelers to be warped to unexpected locations. Use the waypoint to travel to these locations and re-record the data. Beware--you may not end up where you wanted to be.

Client: Darcia (Chamber of Commerce and Industry, Lower Jeuno)Summary: Not all tests are tests of steel. In order to get permission to visit Adoulin, you must record data located in a certain part of the Middle Lands. The Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network will provide your reward.

Client: Nantoto (Merry Minstrel Meadhouse, Lower Jeuno)Summary: For adventurers of appropriate aptitude who have made a name for themselves through Records of Eminence: make a pilgrimage to six telepoints throughout Vana'diel.

Client: Nantoto (Merry Minstrel Meadhouse, Lower Jeuno)Summary: For adventurers of even more appropriate aptitude whose feats in Records of Eminence are widely renowned: travel to the Eldieme Necropolis and shine some light on a few shadows.

Client: Nantoto (Merry Minstrel Meadhouse, Lower Jeuno)Summary: For adventurers of incredible aptitude whose feats in Records of Eminence are household topics of discussion: make some Yagudo High Priests in Castle Oztroja pray to their maker!
Client: Mapitoto (Chocobo Stables, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Hop on board Mapitoto's slightly ornery raptor and head to Batallia Downs. Seek out Syrillia once you have arrived.
Client: Jeridade (Chocobo Stables, Upper Jeuno)Summary: Jeridade has a dream: to create a flying machine for the ages. If you have any leads, be sure to bring them to Mapitoto.
